---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={`About | ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="About Andres Carrillo - full-stack developer from Bolivia" />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>About me</h1>

			<p>
				I'm a full-stack developer from Bolivia. I work mostly with TypeScript, React, Next.js,
				and Node.js, but I've touched a lot of different technologies over the years - from Laravel
				and Vue to Rust, Go, and even Arduino/ESP32 hardware projects.
			</p>

			<p>
				I like building practical things. Most of my projects come from real problems:
				a bank that doesn't offer a QR payment API (so I automated it via ADB),
				marketplace listings with no prices (so I built a marketplace where prices are mandatory),
				manual attendance tracking (so I built a barcode-scanning system).
			</p>

			<p>
				My philosophy is simple: <strong>do it once, do it right</strong>. I'd rather spend
				time building something properly than patching it forever.
			</p>

			<h2>What I've worked on</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>Full-stack web applications (React, Next.js, Laravel, Vue)</li>
				<li>Mobile apps (React Native, Flutter)</li>
				<li>Backend APIs (Node.js, AdonisJS, Express)</li>
				<li>IoT and embedded systems (Arduino, ESP32, Raspberry Pi)</li>
				<li>Automation and scraping tools</li>
				<li>Computer vision (YOLOv9)</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>Get in touch</h2>
			<p>
				Find me on <a href="https://github.com/99arrzel" target="_blank">GitHub</a>.
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
